Please  read  the  documentation set relevant to you (oh go on...
it  took  me  hours  to type it all in!).  A brief summary of the
contents of each file is given below.

README.DOC  -   Hey! that's this file, dude!

DISTRIBUTION.DOC  -  a  quick summary of the terms and conditions
applicable to the distribution of this package.

USER.DOC    -   a description of the AFORTH package for users.

VENDOR.DOC   -   a   description   of   the  AFORTH  package  for
distributors.

REGISTER.DOC    -   a user registration form.

VREGISTER.DOC   -   a vendor registration form.

INSTALL.DOC -   a quick extraction from user.doc.

UsingAFORTH.doc  -  an introduction to FORTH programming, details
of  the  AFORTH interactive environment, tutorials and a guide to
the included example programs.

In the PROGS drawer you should find the following files:

CALENDAR.F  -   an example FORTH application program.
STEPDOWN.F  -   an example of new construct design.
CASE.F      -   a genuinely useful extension construct.
DATAFILE.F  -   an example of reading and writing data.

